    [
      "p",
      {
        "className": "lesson-meta"
      },
      "Lesson 21"
    ],
    [
      "h1",
      {},
      "Possessive Pronouns"
    ]
  ],
  [
    "article",
    {},
    [
      "section",
      {},
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "In Greek, possession is usually expressed using a \"weak\" form of the\n            personal pronoun that follows the noun. To express \"own\" or for\n            stronger emphasis, we use the word",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "δικός"
        ],
        "."
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {},
        "1. The Weak Forms (My, Your, His...)"
      ],
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "These short words always follow the noun and never change their form\n            based on the noun's case—they only match the person and number of\n            the owner."
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "pronoun-grid mt-8"
        },
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "column "
          },
          [
            "h3",
            {},
            "Singular Owner"
          ],
          [
            "ul",
            {},
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "μου"
              ],
              " ",
              "(my)"
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "σου"
              ],
              " ",
              "(your)"
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "του / της / του"
              ],
              " ",
              "(his / her\n                        / its)"
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "column "
          },
          [
            "h3",
            {},
            "Plural Owner"
          ],
          [
            "ul",
            {},
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "μας"
              ],
              " ",
              "(our)"
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "σας"
              ],
              " ",
              "(your [pl])"
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "span",
                {
                  "className": "greek-text"
                },
                "τους"
              ],
              " ",
              "(their)"
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "example-box mt-12 mb-12"
        },
        [
          "h3",
          {},
          "Examples"
        ],
        [
          "ul",
          {},
          [
            "li",
            {},
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "το βιβλίο",
              " ",
              [
                "strong",
                {},
                "μου"
              ]
            ],
            " ",
            "(my book)"
          ],
          [
            "li",
            {},
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "το μολύβι",
              " ",
              [
                "strong",
                {},
                "του"
              ]
            ],
            " ",
            "(his pencil)"
          ],
          [
            "li",
            {},
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "το σκυλί",
              " ",
              [
                "strong",
                {},
                "τους"
              ]
            ],
            " ",
            "(their dog)"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {
          "className": "mt-12"
        },
        "2. Emphatic Possession (δικός)"
      ],
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "The word",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "δικός, δική, δικό"
        ],
        " ",
        "acts like an adjective and\n            is used to say \"mine\" or \"my own\". It must match the gender of the object\n            being possessed."
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "comparison-grid mt-8"
        },
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "card "
          },
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "το δικό μου"
          ],
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "translation"
            },
            "my own / mine"
          ]
        ],
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "card "
          },
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "το δικό σου"
          ],
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "translation"
            },
            "your own / yours"
          ]
        ],
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "card "
          },
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "το δικό του"
          ],
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "translation"
            },
            "his own / his"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "info-box  mt-12 mb-12"
        },
        [
          "h3",
          {},
          "Pro-Tip: The Article"
        ],
        [
          "p",
          {},
          "When using",
          " ",
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "δικός"
          ],
          ", you often need an article\n                before it. Think of it like saying \"the mine own\". Example:",
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "Έχω το δικό μου αυτοκίνητο."
          ],
          " ",
          "(I have my own car)."
        ]
      ]
    ]
  ],
